<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3449] groovyc in 1.6.0 no longer supports &apos;deprecation&apos; attribute on nested javac</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3449</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With Groovy 1.5.1 I used the &apos;deprecation&apos; attribute on &amp;lt;javac&amp;gt; nested within the &amp;lt;groovyc&amp;gt; Ant task to have the compiler spit out deprecated API warnings: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;          &amp;lt;groovyc ...&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            ...&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;javac deprecation=&quot;${javac.deprecation}&quot; .../&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
          &amp;lt;/groovyc&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m trying to upgrade to Groovy 1.6.0 but it complains that &apos;deprecation&apos; is no longer a supported attribute on &amp;lt;javac&amp;gt; (within &amp;lt;groovyc&amp;gt; that is - it still works fine from a regular &amp;lt;javac&amp;gt; call). If I invoke groovyc from AntBuilder (within a &amp;lt;groovy&amp;gt; element in my Ant script), the error goes away but the attribute has no effect. I can&apos;t find any way to get my deprecation warnings back.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Groovy 1.6.0, Ant 1.7.1, Java 1.5.0_16, Windows XP.</environment>
        <key id="12814671">GROOVY-3449</key>
